.TH "check_mft_mirror" 9 "check_mft_mirror" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
check_mft_mirror \- compare contents of the mft mirror with the mft
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" check_mft_mirror
.BI "(ntfs_volume *vol "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vol" 12
ntfs super block describing device whose mft mirror to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return 'true' on success or 'false' on error.

Note, this function also results in the mft mirror runlist being completely
mapped into memory.  The mft mirror write code requires this and will \fBBUG\fP
should it find an unmapped runlist element.
